  "description": "A lighter evening recipe designed to feel comforting without becoming heavy or starch-dense. Broken Wheat Vegetable Pongal brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Dry-roast the moong dal over medium-low heat for 2 minutes.",
    "Cook the grain, dal, salt, and water together until very soft: 4 whistles or 22 minutes on low heat after boiling.",
    "Temper oil with cumin, pepper, ginger, and curry leaves on medium heat for 40 seconds and fold into the pongal.",
    "Quickly saute or add the vegetable garnish as specified and serve hot."
